data.enText: to walk or travel around an area without any definite aim or direction

data.chText: 绵羊可以在这片地上自由走动。
data.enText: The sheep are allowed to roam freely on this land.
to roam the countryside/the streets, etc.
to move slowly over every part of sb/sth

data.chText: 他聚精会神地上下打量她。

ex.chText: 漫步乡间，你会发现很多乐趣。
ex.enText: You will find a lot of fun when you ramble in the country.

synonyms.bx: 尤指为消遣而在乡间闲逛。

ex.chText: 在他的别墅里，狗可以四处走动。
ex.enText: Dogs are allowed to roam freely in his villa.

ex.chText: 小孩子晚上不应该在街上游荡。
ex.enText: Children shall not roam the streets at night.
A couple of lovers roam the countryside.

synonyms.bx: 常指长时间没有目的或方向地游荡。

ex.chText: 警方已经抓住了在乡村流窜的那些盗贼。
ex.enText: The police have caught the thieves who roved the countryside.

ex.chText: 作为一名全国各地跑的推销员，他很少有时间陪伴家人。
ex.enText: As a salesman roving the country, he has little time to spend with his family.

synonyms.bx: 指到各处游历、走动等，无明确的目的地。

ex.chText: 她和朋友们有说有笑地溜达着。
ex.enText: She and her friends were strolling along, talking and laughing.

ex.chText: 他喜欢晚饭后在海滩散步。
ex.enText: He likes to stroll along the beach after supper.

tr: move about aimlessly or without any destination, often in search of food or employment
example: The cattle roam across the prairie
the laborers drift from one town to the next
They rolled from town to town

value.def: If you roam an area or roam around it, you wander or travel around it without having a particular purpose.

example.tran: 光脚丫的孩子们在街上游荡。

example.ex: They're roaming around the country shooting at anything that moves...
example.tran: 他们在乡下到处转悠，看到活动的东西就开枪。

example.ex: Farmers were encouraged to keep their livestock in pens rather than letting them roam freely.
example.tran: 鼓励农民们把家畜关进栏圈，而不是让它们到处乱跑。
